parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause loss of control, uneven tire wear, and noise, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Strange popping sound when turning or backing up
rear axle falls out from under the car
vehicle jerks while driving
uneven tire wear
noise in the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the passenger seat belt can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the belt may not provide adequate restraint or may even cause harm to the occupant.
symptoms: The passenger seat belt becomes extremely tight and won't release
the belt won't release when the door is opened
the belt must be manually unlatched or the vehicle must be restarted to release
the belt is very loose and won't retract
the belt can cause physical harm to the occupant
such as taking off a finger tip.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The serpentine belt comes off while driving
especially when driving through large puddles of water
making it difficult to steer the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature head gasket failure can cause engine oil contamination, overheating, and excessive coolant usage, leading to engine damage and potential failure.
symptoms: Engine oil contamination
no heat
excessive coolant usage
and potentially engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a loss of power, overheating, and potentially lead to a vehicle fire, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine check light comes on
temperature gauge rises
unusual engine noises
and smoke coming from the back of the vehicle.
